18.title: The Idiots
18.plot: It's another Lars Von Trier film. This time, Oan looks at one of Von Trier's entries into the Dogme-95 movement, and tries to follow the strict rules set forth by the movement when doing his review. Hi-jinx to follow.

19.title: Ken Park
19.plot: Oancitizen critiques Ken Park, a disturbing film that follows four teenagers and their violent, sexual escapades. It causes Oan to hate the small town of Vaselia, California, where the film is set, and turns to Diamanda Hagan for help.

20.title: 9 Songs
20.plot: Oancitizen watches a film that follows a young couple who attend concerts and in between, have unsimulated sex, and in a new position each time. The film leaves Oan feeling very sexually frustrated.

21.title: Vase De Noces
21.plot: Ralph finally gives in and reviews the notorious pig-loving movie, which nearly pushes him to his breaking point.

22.title: The Anatomy of Hell
22.plot: Oancitizen reviews a sexually graphic film, which explores every biological and natural aspect of the female anatomy and the inherent fear of it felt by men.

23.title: Shortbus
23.plot: The 'Citizen checks out a movie that is the epitome of sex on film. A cinematic orgy for the ages.

24.title: Melancholia
24.plot: Ralph Oancitizen celebrates his 50th episode by looking at the 2011 Lars Von Trier drama/sci-fi Melancholia. He praises Kirsten Dunst, but special praise is for Udo Kier. Several of his friends pop up unexpectedly to congratulate Oan on making it to 50 episodes.

1.title: Nightwatching/Rembrandt's J'Accuse
1.plot: Oancitizen travels back to his homeland in Holland, where he regals his viewers with fond memories and the histories of the Dutch, and even pays his respects to Rembrandt and reviews two subpar movies about his work.

2.title: Mister Lonely
2.plot: The 'citizen revisits an old "friend", Harmony Korine, and takes a look at one of his more normal-looking films.

3.title: Dead Man
3.plot: Oancitizen looks at the works of Jim Jarmusch again, and due to the recently released Lone Ranger movie with Johnny Depp, Oan takes a look at an early Depp/Jarmusch collaboration. Hijinks to follow.

4.title: Room in Rome
4.plot: Oancitizen reviews the sultry Room in Rome and finds, being straight and all, that he can't judge the film objectively. Luckily, his sidekick Ven has his back.

5.title: Yeelen
5.plot: Oancitizen reviews a film that tells one all they need to know about the continent of Africa.

6.title: Shame
6.plot: The movie looked at today is Steve McQueen's 2011 drama Shame. Oancitizen analyzes the protagonist's sex addiction, complains about the overuse of long-takes and vents his frustrations about how and why New York always seems to show up in various songs, books and movies.
